Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced). Trim, peel, and
cut @carrots{6%ounce}(trimmed, peeled, and cut into 1/4-inch-thick rounds). Peel and
mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}(minced). Remove and discard any large stems
from @kale{4%ounce}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pot{} over medium-high
heat. Add onion and carrots; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until veggies are lightly browned and slightly softened,
~{4-6%minutes}.

Once veggies have cooked for ~{2-3%minutes}, add @ground beef{10%ounce}; season
with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and
cooked through and veggies are slightly softened, ~{4-6%minutes}. TIP: If there's
excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Stir @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon} and garlic into pot with veggies. Cook until
fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce}, @veggie stock concentrate{3}, and @water{3%cups}
and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook until
carrots are just softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Once carrots are just softened, stir in @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce} and kale.
Cook until couscous is tender and kale is wilted, ~{8-10%minutes}. Taste and
season generously with salt and pepper.

While soup cooks, halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise.

Place @butter{2%tablespoon} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until
just softened, ~{10-15%seconds}. Stir in @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} and
season with salt and pepper.

Toast baguette halves on a #grill{} or in a #toaster oven{}, then spread cut sides
with garlic butter. Halve each piece on a diagonal.

Divide soup between bowls. Sprinkle with @parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} and a pinch of
@chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste. Serve with garlic bread on the side.